jexer.bits

Class Cell

  • java.lang.Object
    • jexer.bits.CellAttributes
      • jexer.bits.Cell

  • public class Cell
extends CellAttributes
    This class represents a single text cell or bit of image on the screen.

      • mixImageId

        public void mixImageId(Cell other)
        "Mix" the imageId of another Cell into this cell. When two cells both have imageId's set, the mixture of them should be a deterministic combination such that one can compare a sequence of "mixed" cells and know (within a high degree of likelihood) that they produced the same final image.
        Parameters:
        other - the other cell

      • mixImageId

        public void mixImageId(int operation)
        "Mix" the imageId of another operation into this cell. When a cell has its imageId set, the mixture of it and other operations should be a deterministic combination such that one can compare a sequence of cell + operations and know (within a high degree of likelihood) that they produced the same final image.
        Parameters:
        operation - the operation to mix in, typically a color translucent RGB that was blitted over or under this image

      • flattenImage

        public void flattenImage(boolean overGlyph,
                         Backend backend)
        Flatten the image on this cell by rendering it either onto the background color, or generating the glyph and rendering over that.
        Parameters:
        overGlyph - if true, render over the glyph
        backend - the backend that can obtain the correct background color
